This paper deals with image inpainting using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel method for instance separation, which involves measuring the independence of two image regions and maximizing it, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning (cs.AI). The method also involves leveraging implicit knowledge of image composition, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for its proposed method, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with microscopy images, which is a topic in graphics (cs.GR).
